## When adding the default transfer UI

Drop `<TransferBubble />` anywhere in the component tree — it renders as a fixed-position floating overlay:

```typescript
import {TransferBubble} from '@nu-art/file-upload-frontend';

// In any rendered component tree:
<TransferBubble />
```

The bubble auto-shows when transfers begin and auto-hides after completion. It subscribes to `OnFileTransferStateChanged` — no props or wiring needed.

When both uploads and downloads are active simultaneously, the bubble shows direction tabs ("Uploads" / "Downloads") at the top of the tray. When only one direction is active, no tabs are shown.

### Theming the bubble

All styles use CSS custom properties prefixed `--ts-tb-*`. Override at the app's root to theme:

```scss
.ts-transfer-bubble {
	--ts-tb-color-primary: #7c3aed;
	--ts-tb-color-success: #059669;
	--ts-tb-fab-size: 56px;
	--ts-tb-tray-width: 380px;
	--ts-tb-radius: 12px;
}
```

All component classes are BEM-namespaced under `.ts-transfer-bubble__*` — override any selector at the app level.

